casebody.data:
Argued and submitted August 7, 1991, ANTONIO A. GUTIERREZ, Appellant, v. Manfred (Fred) MAASS, Respondent. (90 C 11458; CA A68490) 825 P2d 657 Jay Edwards, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for appellant. Timothy A. Sylwester, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Dave Frohnmayer, Attorney General, and Virginia L. Linder, Solicitor General, Salem. PER CURIAM

affirmed February 12,

reconsideration denied April 15,

petition for review pending 1992

Before Warren, Presiding Judge, and Riggs and Edmonds, Judges.
